    "text": "A pounding heart during all-out sprints is your cardiovascular system doing exactly its job; hard intervals push heart rate near max, and feeling it thump, even in your ears, is normal at that intensity. Nothing about that description says stop training. You also logged a generous 485 minutes of sleep, about 8.1 h, so today is fine for a workout; if the legs are heavy from the sprints, make it an easier spin or strength day and go hard again tomorrow. The distinction worth knowing: pounding that starts during max effort and settles as you ease off is expected, while a heartbeat that races or flutters at rest, skips erratically, or comes with chest pain or lightheadedness is a different thing and worth getting checked. Yours, as described, is the normal kind.",
